 practice; develops techniques to develop evidence-based policy in the housing association sector; discusses the implications of innovating in regulated public service industries. Managing public services innovation is essential reading for housing industry and public management professionals, policy makers and academics in housing, business and public management departments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aHousing managementzEngland. 0aHousingxSocieties, etczEngland. 0aHousingzEnglandxSocieties, etc. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / City Planning & Urban Development.2bisacsh1 aJeanes, Emma L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRowlands, Robert O., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847425263423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847425263/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles